                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Japanese Chargé</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 258.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In answer to your note No. 12, of the 5th
                    instant, I have to inform you that the American ambassador to Russia was
                    instructed by telegraph, on the 7th instant, to hand over the Japanese legation
                    at St. Petersburg to Mr. Tano, third secretary of legation, who has been ordered
                    by Mr. Motono, the new Japanese minister to Russia, to proceed directly to St.
                    Petersburg on the 8th instant.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
